The paper proposes a framework for integrating procedural knowledge into the Linked Data Cloud, which involves representing generic know-how as Linked Data and automatically acquiring this representation from existing resources on the Web. This involves techniques from artificial intelligence (AI) for automatically acquiring knowledge, information retrieval (IR) for retrieving relevant resources, and databases (DB) for representing and querying the data. Additionally, the paper discusses the results of applying the framework to a real-world scenario, which involves aspects of cybersecurity (CY) and software engineering (SE).
